commit.title: Add a `strategy` tactic
commit.message:
Add a `strategy` tactic

Useful for guarding calls to `unfold` or `cbv` to ensure that, e.g.,
`Opaque foo` doesn't break some automation which tries to unfold `foo`.

Add some timeouts to the strategy success file

We should not run into issues, because we are not really testing how
long these take.  We could just as well use `Timeout 60` or longer, we
just want to make sure the file dies more quickly rather than taking
over 10^100 steps.

Use Global.set_strategy more directly, as per reivew request

Useful for guarding calls to `unfold` or `cbv` to ensure that, e.g.,
`Opaque foo` doesn't break some automation which tries to unfold `foo`.

Add some timeouts to the strategy success file

We should not run into issues, because we are not really testing how
long these take.  We could just as well use `Timeout 60` or longer, we
just want to make sure the file dies more quickly rather than taking
over 10^100 steps.

Use Global.set_strategy more directly, as per reivew request
